title: What can I do if my phone fails to access the Internet?
answer:
Insert a SIM card into your phone. The phone then automatically configures APN settings. 

 To view the APN settings, go to Settings > More > Wireless & networks > Mobile networks > Access Point Names. 

 [If the parameter settings are incorrect, touch ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=111081). From the displayed option menu, choose Reset to default.]()
